Imperial Crown Trading Offices Raided Amid Anglo American Rights Dispute

-- B y   J a n a   M a r a i s
-- 
2011-07-27T14:52:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/imperial-crown-trading-offices-raided-amid-anglo-american-rights-dispute.html
Imperial Crown Trading 289 (Pty)
Ltd., which is in a dispute with  Anglo American Plc (AAL) ’s  Kumba Iron
Ore Ltd. (KIO)  unit over prospecting rights, said its offices were
raided today by South African investigators.  Offices of the Department of Mineral Resources in Pretoria
and Kimberley were also raided by police investigators known as
the Hawks, Ronnie Mendelow, a lawyer for ICT, said by mobile
phone from Johannesburg. He couldn’t immediately provide more
details on the raids.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jana Marais in Johannesburg at 
 jmarais@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  